––– comment –––
ALTER TABLE REBUILD SECONDARY must work after OPTIMIZE merges RT disk chunks and renames the result.
––– block: ../base/start-searchd –––
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SET GLOBAL auto_optimize=0; DROP TABLE IF EXISTS rebuild_si; CREATE TABLE rebuild_si(tag int) optimize_cutoff='1'; INSERT INTO rebuild_si VALUES(1,1); FLUSH RAMCHUNK rebuild_si; INSERT INTO rebuild_si VALUES(2,2); FLUSH RAMCHUNK rebuild_si; OPTIMIZE TABLE rebuild_si OPTION sync=1; ALTER TABLE rebuild_si REBUILD SECONDARY;" && echo OK
––– output –––
OK
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -NBe "SHOW TABLE rebuild_si STATUS LIKE 'disk_chunks'\G"
––– output –––
*************************** 1. row ***************************
disk_chunks
1
––– comment –––
SI disabled by an attribute update after OPTIMIZE chunk rename should be saved to the renamed .spidx file.
This currently documents the unfixed MCL behavior: the disabled state is lost after restart because SI meta is saved through the stale pre-rename path.
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SET GLOBAL auto_optimize=0; DROP TABLE IF EXISTS rebuild_si_meta; CREATE TABLE rebuild_si_meta(tag int) optimize_cutoff='1'; INSERT INTO rebuild_si_meta VALUES(1,1); FLUSH RAMCHUNK rebuild_si_meta; INSERT INTO rebuild_si_meta VALUES(2,2); FLUSH RAMCHUNK rebuild_si_meta; OPTIMIZE TABLE rebuild_si_meta OPTION sync=1; UPDATE rebuild_si_meta SET tag=3 WHERE id=1; SHOW WARNINGS;"
––– output –––
+---------+------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Level   | Code | Message                                                                                                   |
+---------+------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| warning | 1000 | secondary index disabled for attribute(s) 'tag' after attribute update; run ALTER TABLE REBUILD SECONDARY |
+---------+------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW TABLE rebuild_si_meta INDEXES;"
––– output –––
+------+--------+---------+---------+
| Name | Type   | Enabled | Percent |
+------+--------+---------+---------+
| tag  | uint32 | 0       | 100     |
| id   | int64  | 1       | 100     |
+------+--------+---------+---------+
––– input –––
if find /var/lib/manticore/rebuild_si_meta -maxdepth 1 -name '*.tmp.spidx' | grep -q .; then echo "stale tmp spidx"; else echo "no stale tmp spidx"; fi
––– output –––
no stale tmp spidx
––– input –––
stdbuf -oL searchd --stopwait > /dev/null
